6
00:03:38,751 --> 00:03:45,625
ON THE BASIS OF THE PREVIOUS TESTIMONY.

7
00:03:45,658 --> 00:03:49,662
Attorney: IT'S ALL IN THE FILE, YOUR HONOR.

8
00:03:49,696 --> 00:03:51,698
ACUTE PARANOIA, SCHIZOPHRENIA.

9
00:03:51,731 --> 00:03:54,033
MY CLIENT DOESN'T EVEN REMEMBER

10
00:03:54,067 --> 00:03:56,669
COMMITTING THE CRIME IN QUESTION.

11
00:03:56,703 --> 00:03:57,971
EVEN A POLYGRAPH PROVED THAT.

12
00:03:58,004 --> 00:04:01,374
- OBJECTION, YOUR HONOR. INADMISSIBLE. - SUSTAINED.

13
00:04:01,407 --> 00:04:03,610
WE ALL KNOW EVEN POLYGRAPHS LIE.

14
00:04:03,643 --> 00:04:05,979
THANKS FOR THAT PIECE OF INFORMATION. APPRECIATE IT.

15
00:04:06,012 --> 00:04:07,580
IN ANY STAGE, YOUR HONOR,

16
00:04:07,614 --> 00:04:09,549
I DON'T KNOW HOW RELEVANT

17
00:04:09,582 --> 00:04:13,419
MR. McNAMARA'S SO-CALLED ECHO PET SCAN ANALYSIS

18
00:04:13,453 --> 00:04:14,554
- IS GONNA BE. - I CAN MAKE IT VERY RELEVANT,

19
00:04:14,587 --> 00:04:17,657
IF COUNSEL WILL JUST GIVE ME AN OPPORTUNITY TO STEP UP.

20
00:04:17,690 --> 00:04:20,560
- STEP UP. - THANK YOU.

21
00:04:25,765 --> 00:04:30,637
THE DEFENDANT DID, INDEED, MURDER STACY SMITH.

22
00:04:30,670 --> 00:04:32,639
THE ONLY QUESTION IS,

23
00:04:32,672 --> 00:04:35,975
WAS HE INSANE AT THE TIME?

24
00:04:38,011 --> 00:04:40,813
I CALL DR. LAZARRE.

25
00:05:17,750 --> 00:05:20,653
HELLO, DOCTOR. YOU KNOW THE PROCEDURE.

26
00:05:20,687 --> 00:05:22,955
YOU GOT FIVE MINUTES.

27
00:05:40,173 --> 00:05:41,741
HELLO, JONAS.

28
00:05:41,774 --> 00:05:43,910
FINALLY GETTING TO SEE ME.

29
00:05:46,746 --> 00:05:49,916
THEY'RE SAYING IT'S HARDER FOR YOU SHRINKS TO GET INTO THIS PLACE

30
00:05:49,949 --> 00:05:53,019
THAN IT IS FOR US SICK FUCKS TO GET OUT.

31
00:05:53,052 --> 00:05:55,388
YET HERE YOU ARE.

32
00:05:57,056 --> 00:05:58,925
INTRIGUING, ISN'T IT?

33
00:05:58,958 --> 00:06:01,994
YOU WERE IN COURT.

34
00:06:02,028 --> 00:06:05,798
YOU SAW THE EVIDENCE, YOU AND YOUR FANCY LAWYERS.

35
00:06:05,832 --> 00:06:07,633
BUT THAT WASN'T GOOD ENOUGH FOR YOU.

36
00:06:07,667 --> 00:06:10,002
HUH?

37
00:06:10,036 --> 00:06:14,874
YOU STILL HAD TO COME HERE AND SQUEEZE IT OUT OF ME.

38
00:06:14,907 --> 00:06:17,877
DO YOU FEEL ANY REMORSE?

39
00:06:17,910 --> 00:06:19,912
LET ME SEE. REMORSE.

40
00:06:19,946 --> 00:06:24,250
I'M SORRY I CUT POOR SARAH LETTINGS INTO SO MANY PIECES,

41
00:06:24,283 --> 00:06:26,719
BUT THE BITCH HAD IT COMING, I SWEAR.

42
00:06:28,087 --> 00:06:30,423
MAN, SHE HAD A BEAUTIFUL SCREAM.

43
00:06:31,858 --> 00:06:33,926
IT'S A SHAME.

44
00:06:33,960 --> 00:06:37,029
YOU HAVE DOUBTS, DON'T YOU?

45
00:06:37,063 --> 00:06:40,266
BIG FUCKING DOUBTS.

46
00:06:40,299 --> 00:06:42,835
BUT NOT ME. NOT WHERE I'M GOING.

47
00:06:42,869 --> 00:06:44,871
THERE WAS A SEAT WAITING FOR ME

48
00:06:44,904 --> 00:06:49,142
DOWN IN HELL THE MINUTE I WAS BORN, DOC.

49
00:06:49,175 --> 00:06:51,944
ME, MY LIFE...

50
00:06:51,978 --> 00:06:55,581
WOMEN, DEATH.

51
00:06:57,016 --> 00:07:00,720
THIS PLACE, THESE CHAINS.

52
00:07:00,753 --> 00:07:03,923
ALL PREAMBLE. 35 YEARS OF PURGATORY

53
00:07:03,956 --> 00:07:05,525
JUST TO SEE HOW MANY POOR SOULS

54
00:07:05,558 --> 00:07:07,960
I CAN DRAG DOWN WITH ME.

55
00:07:07,994 --> 00:07:09,896
I'M GOING TO THE SHOW NOW,

56
00:07:09,929 --> 00:07:12,965
AND YOU CAN'T TOUCH ME THERE.

57
00:07:14,167 --> 00:07:17,003
NOBODY CAN.

58
00:07:17,036 --> 00:07:18,838
BUT YOU.

59
00:07:18,871 --> 00:07:21,974
YOU'RE STUCK HERE WITH YOUR MISERABLE DOUBTS.

60
00:07:22,008 --> 00:07:24,811
( Jonas sighs )

61
00:07:24,844 --> 00:07:26,979
I KNOW WHY YOU CAME HERE.

62
00:07:27,013 --> 00:07:28,781
I KNOW WHY YOU CAME HERE.

63
00:07:28,815 --> 00:07:30,983
I CAN SEE RIGHT THROUGH YOU.

64
00:07:32,819 --> 00:07:37,123
SOMETHING... SOMETHING IS EATING YOU ALIVE.

65
00:07:37,156 --> 00:07:38,324
WHAT ARE YOU GETTING AT?

66
00:07:38,357 --> 00:07:40,726
YOU'RE NOT HERE TO SAVE ME.

67
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:43,029
YOU'RE HERE TO SAVE YOURSELF.

68
00:07:44,997 --> 00:07:47,633
YOU'RE HERE TO SAVE YOURSELF!

69
00:07:47,667 --> 00:07:49,936
YOU'RE HERE TO SAVE YOURSELF!

70
00:07:49,969 --> 00:07:51,871
- PLEASE... - YOU'RE HERE TO SAVE YOURSELF!

71
00:07:51,904 --> 00:07:53,906
JUST GIVE ME ONE MORE MINUTE.

72
00:07:56,309 --> 00:07:57,677
JONAS!

73
00:08:08,020 --> 00:08:09,121
SHH!

74
00:08:09,155 --> 00:08:11,757
I'M NOT GONNA HURT YOU.

75
00:08:11,791 --> 00:08:13,826
I'M NOT GONNA HURT YOU.

76
00:08:13,860 --> 00:08:18,097
IAN, LOOK INSIDE YOURSELF.

77
00:08:26,172 --> 00:08:29,008
JUST LIKE OLD TIMES, EH, BUDDY? JUST LIKE OLD TIMES.

78
00:08:29,041 --> 00:08:32,745
THE AMERICAN JUSTICE SYSTEM! WHOO!

79
00:08:32,778 --> 00:08:35,748
KNOCK OFF ALL THE CRAZIES. LOCK 'EM UP.

80
00:08:35,781 --> 00:08:38,017
YOU SET ME UP.

81
00:08:38,050 --> 00:08:41,053
TURNSTILE TO NOWHERE SYSTEM.

82
00:08:41,087 --> 00:08:43,022
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

83
00:08:43,055 --> 00:08:44,957
NOTHIN'. YOU SUMMED IT UP PERFECTLY.

84
00:08:44,991 --> 00:08:47,393
YOU'VE BEEN KEEPING AN AWFUL LOT TO YOURSELF LATELY.

85
00:08:47,426 --> 00:08:49,061
YOU ALL RIGHT? YOU OKAY?

86
00:08:49,095 --> 00:08:51,097
- YEAH, I'M FINE. - YOU'RE FINE? YOU'RE SURE?

87
00:08:51,130 --> 00:08:53,099
- I SAID I'M FINE. - ALL RIGHT, HE'S FINE.

88
00:08:53,132 --> 00:08:55,868
COUNSELOR, GENTLEMEN, WHAT'LL IT BE?

89
00:08:55,902 --> 00:08:57,570
MARTINI EXTRA DRY.

90
00:08:59,972 --> 00:09:02,742
YOU KNOW WHAT? WHY DON'T YOU MAKE THAT TWO?

91
00:09:02,775 --> 00:09:05,011
ONE FOR MY OLD PAL HERE. THE DOC, HUH?

92
00:09:05,044 --> 00:09:07,179
WHAT DO YOU SAY? ONE FOR OLD TIME'S SAKE?

93
00:09:07,213 --> 00:09:10,249
JUST COFFEE.

94
00:09:10,283 --> 00:09:12,218
STIRRED OR SHAKEN?

95
00:09:12,251 --> 00:09:14,387
( imitates James Bond ) SHAKEN, NOT STIRRED.

96
00:09:21,861 --> 00:09:23,896
I'M SORRY YOU LOST YOUR GRANT.

97
00:09:23,930 --> 00:09:26,098
TERESA TOLD ME.

98
00:09:26,132 --> 00:09:28,634
I KNOW HOW MUCH THAT RESEARCH MEANT TO YOU.

99
00:09:28,668 --> 00:09:31,237
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

100
00:09:31,270 --> 00:09:33,906
SOMEBODY UP THERE ON THAT BOARD...

101
00:09:33,940 --> 00:09:36,075
- MARTY. - DOESN'T LIKE ME.

102
00:09:36,108 --> 00:09:37,710
COUNSELOR, YOUR DRINK.

103
00:09:37,743 --> 00:09:39,045
I'D LIKE TO CHANGE MY ORDER.

104
00:09:39,078 --> 00:09:40,379
SCOTCH, DOUBLE.

105
00:09:40,413 --> 00:09:42,882
I WANNA MAKE A TOAST

106
00:09:42,915 --> 00:09:44,784
TO ALL THE THINGS THAT MIGHT HAVE BEEN.

107
00:09:45,851 --> 00:09:47,320
COME ON, JOE.

108
00:09:47,353 --> 00:09:50,089
- FOR OLD TIME'S SAKE. - WHY DON'T WE DO THIS TOMORROW?

109
00:09:50,122 --> 00:09:52,391
I GOTTA GET BACK TO THE OFFICE.

110
00:10:06,472 --> 00:10:09,241
YOU ALWAYS GOT WHAT YOU WANTED,

111
00:10:09,275 --> 00:10:12,778
ESPECIALLY WHEN IT COMES TO WOMEN.

112
00:10:12,812 --> 00:10:14,213
DON'T START WITH THAT, IAN.

113
00:10:14,246 --> 00:10:16,015
DON'T YOU START WITH THAT.

114
00:10:16,048 --> 00:10:17,817
DON'T START WITH THAT.

115
00:10:17,850 --> 00:10:20,119
YEAH, YOU'RE RIGHT. DON'T START, DON'T START.

116
00:10:20,152 --> 00:10:22,922
DON'T START ANYTHING AGAIN.

117
00:10:22,955 --> 00:10:25,725
- DON'T START... - I'M YOUR FRIEND.

118
00:10:25,758 --> 00:10:27,860
- I WANNA HELP YOU. - I DON'T WANT ANY HELP.

119
00:10:27,893 --> 00:10:30,096
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.

120
00:10:30,129 --> 00:10:31,697
I DON'T WANT ANY FUCKIN' HELP.

121
00:10:31,731 --> 00:10:33,132
WHAT DO YOU WANT? WHAT, WHAT?

122
00:10:33,165 --> 00:10:34,900
TELL ME WHAT YOU WANT.

123
00:10:34,934 --> 00:10:36,802
I WANT TO BELIEVE IN SOMETHING.

124
00:10:36,836 --> 00:10:39,071
IAN, WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

125
00:10:39,105 --> 00:10:41,173
I GOTTA GO.

126
00:10:44,043 --> 00:10:46,345
I KNOW WHERE YOU'RE GOIN'.

127
00:10:46,379 --> 00:10:48,381
I'M NOT GOIN' THERE.

128
00:10:54,420 --> 00:10:59,191
Woman: I DON'T KNOW. MAYBE IT'S JUST ME.

129
00:10:59,225 --> 00:11:03,295
MAYBE SOME PEOPLE ARE JUST BORN BROKEN.

130
00:11:03,329 --> 00:11:06,332
BUT I'M NOT CRAZY, AND I DIDN'T TRY TO KILL MYSELF

131
00:11:06,365 --> 00:11:08,834
TO GET ATTENTION OR TO MAKE A POINT.

132
00:11:08,868 --> 00:11:11,737
I JUST WANTED TO FEEL BETTER.

133
00:11:11,771 --> 00:11:14,840
I'M SICK OF EVERYBODY TELLING ME TO JUST GET OUT OF BED

134
00:11:14,874 --> 00:11:18,110
AND DO SOMETHING FOR MYSELF.

135
00:11:18,144 --> 00:11:20,046
IT'S LIKE, ALL OF A SUDDEN,

136
00:11:20,079 --> 00:11:23,315
I'M JUST GONNA BE HAPPY. MY TROUBLES WILL JUST GO AWAY.

137
00:11:23,349 --> 00:11:28,287
HOW CAN THEY SAY THAT WHEN THEY DON'T KNOW WHAT IT FEELS LIKE?

138
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:31,791
COULD YOU TELL ME WHAT THE PAIN IS,

139
00:11:31,824 --> 00:11:33,225
OR WHERE IT COMES FROM?

140
00:11:33,259 --> 00:11:35,461
I DON'T KNOW WHERE IT COMES FROM.

141
00:11:35,494 --> 00:11:38,230
IT'S NOT LIKE IT'S PHYSICAL PAIN.

142
00:11:38,264 --> 00:11:42,535
I DON'T FEEL LIKE SOMEONE'S STEPPING ON MY FOOT ALL THE TIME.

143
00:11:44,270 --> 00:11:47,039
IT'S THE KIND OF PAIN YOU FEEL LIKE,

144
00:11:47,073 --> 00:11:51,510
WHEN YOU'RE A KID, AND YOU'RE SCARED OF THE DARK,

145
00:11:51,544 --> 00:11:54,046
AND YOUR MOM MAKES YOU SLEEP WITH THE LIGHTS OFF

146
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:57,083
SO YOU'LL GET OVER IT.

147
00:11:57,116 --> 00:11:59,218
SO YOU LIE AWAKE IN THE DARK,

148
00:11:59,251 --> 00:12:01,120
JUST TERRIFIED OF THINGS YOU CAN'T SEE,

149
00:12:01,153 --> 00:12:04,023
BUT TOO SCARED OF YOUR PARENTS

150
00:12:04,056 --> 00:12:07,026
TO JUST TURN THE LIGHTS ON.

151
00:12:07,059 --> 00:12:09,328
SO YOU STAY AWAKE THE WHOLE NIGHT,

152
00:12:09,361 --> 00:12:12,298
WAITING FOR THE SUN TO COME UP,

153
00:12:12,331 --> 00:12:15,434
HOPING YOUR MOM'S GONNA COME IN AND CHECK ON YOU.

154
00:12:18,170 --> 00:12:20,573
IT'S HARD FOR ME TO EXPLAIN IT.

155
00:12:20,606 --> 00:12:24,276
IT'S LIKE... IT'S LIKE THE SUN NEVER CAME UP,

156
00:12:24,310 --> 00:12:27,012
AND NOBODY EVER CAME BACK FOR ME.

157
00:12:27,046 --> 00:12:30,316
SO I'M JUST STUCK WHERE I AM.

158
00:12:30,349 --> 00:12:33,586
IS IT SO UNREASONABLE TO THINK THAT, AT SOME POINT,

159
00:12:33,619 --> 00:12:36,288
SOMEBODY WOULD GET SO TIRED OF BEING THAT WAY

160
00:12:36,322 --> 00:12:40,459
THAT THEY WOULD JUST WANNA END IT?

161
00:12:40,493 --> 00:12:43,596
I SAW A MOVIE ONCE WHERE A PERSON SAID,

162
00:12:43,629 --> 00:12:46,932
"YOU CAN'T CHANGE A BAD HAND OF CARDS.

163
00:12:46,966 --> 00:12:49,168
SOMETIMES, YOU JUST HAVE TO FOLD."

164
00:12:57,676 --> 00:13:00,479
HEY, HEY, HEY. COME ON, COME ON, CUT THAT OUT.

165
00:13:00,513 --> 00:13:02,414
YOU GUYS CAN FAWN ALL OVER EACH OTHER LATER.

166
00:13:02,448 --> 00:13:05,184
THIS GUY MICHELSON, HE'S GOT SO MUCH MONEY.

167
00:13:05,217 --> 00:13:07,520
YOU GUYS, COME ON, IT'S GETTING LATE.

168
00:13:07,553 --> 00:13:10,189
NO! NO, NO, NO, NO. YOU CAN'T GO. YOU JUST GOT HERE.

169
00:13:10,222 --> 00:13:14,126
ALL RIGHT, IT'S OKAY. YOU STAY. I UNDERSTAND.

170
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:17,229
BUT I'M TIRED, SO I'M GOING HOME, OKAY?

171
00:13:18,964 --> 00:13:20,900
THANK YOU.

172
00:13:20,933 --> 00:13:23,135
SEE YOU LATER.

173
00:13:25,004 --> 00:13:27,173
ARE YOU SURE YOU'RE OKAY TO DRIVE?

174
00:13:27,206 --> 00:13:28,674
( all laughing )

175
00:13:28,707 --> 00:13:31,076
YEAH, I'M FINE, I'M FINE.

176
00:13:31,110 --> 00:13:34,013
I'M A BIG GIRL. SEE YA LATER.

177
00:13:34,046 --> 00:13:35,981
- BYE, JOE. - BYE, WENDY.

178
00:13:41,353 --> 00:13:47,059
I'M SORRY. JUST EXCUSE ME FOR ONE SECOND, OKAY?

179
00:14:27,032 --> 00:14:29,101
STARTING KINDA EARLY, AREN'T YOU, DOC?

180
00:14:32,004 --> 00:14:34,373
WENDY!!

181
00:14:59,431 --> 00:15:03,335
HELENE... CANCEL ALL...

182
00:15:03,369 --> 00:15:06,405
APPOINTMENTS FOR THIS AFTERNOON.

183
00:15:06,438 --> 00:15:09,675
YOU DON'T HAVE ANY APPOINTMENTS THIS AFTERNOON, DOCTOR.

184
00:15:25,024 --> 00:15:27,359
( phone ringing )

185
00:15:27,393 --> 00:15:29,662
TERESA LAZARRE'S OFFICE. THIS IS ANNA SPEAKING.

186
00:15:29,695 --> 00:15:32,464
YES, HELLO. MAY I SPEAK WITH MY WIFE, PLEASE?

187
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:37,469
TERESA, IT'S IAN.

188
00:15:43,642 --> 00:15:45,511
YOU KNOW WHAT? TELL HIM I'M NOT HERE.

189
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:51,350
IAN, SHE DOESN'T WANNA TALK TO YOU, OKAY?

190
00:15:51,383 --> 00:15:53,452
- JUST ASK HER TO COME TO THE PHONE. - NO, IAN.

191
00:15:53,485 --> 00:15:56,522
I DON'T WANNA TALK TO YOU. I WANNA TALK TO MY WIFE.

192
00:15:56,555 --> 00:15:58,223
DON'T YELL, IAN.

193
00:15:58,257 --> 00:16:00,726
- DON'T FUCKING HANG UP ON ME! - ( glass shatters )

194
00:16:00,759 --> 00:16:04,630
PUT MY GODDAMN WIFE ON THE PHONE, GODDAMN YOU!

195
00:16:04,663 --> 00:16:06,398
DOCTOR?

196
00:16:17,676 --> 00:16:20,045
JOE, THESE ARE READY FOR YOUR SIGNATURE.

197
00:16:20,079 --> 00:16:22,314
AND DR. IAN LAZARRE'S OFFICE IS ON LINE TWO.

198
00:16:22,348 --> 00:16:24,483
SOUNDS IMPORTANT.

199
00:16:27,252 --> 00:16:29,488
YEAH, HELENE, HI. IT'S JOE.

200
00:16:33,559 --> 00:16:35,427
ALL RIGHT, CALL HIS EX-WIFE.

201
00:16:36,729 --> 00:16:38,864
JOE, YOU HAVE A MEETING WITH KRAVITZ IN TEN MINUTES.

202
00:16:38,897 --> 00:16:41,033
STALL HIM, ROSIE.

203
00:16:52,444 --> 00:16:54,880
I DIDN'T KNOW WHO ELSE TO CALL. THERE WAS THIS BIG CRASH.

204
00:16:54,913 --> 00:16:57,249
DOES HE HAVE ANY EXTRA KEYS?

205
00:16:57,282 --> 00:16:59,184
- WHAT? - KEYS, GODDAMN IT. KEYS!

206
00:16:59,218 --> 00:17:01,220
I DON'T KNOW. HE NEVER GAVE ME ANY.

207
00:17:01,253 --> 00:17:03,188
GET OUT OF THE WAY.

208
00:17:08,594 --> 00:17:09,528
JESUS CHRIST.

209
00:17:09,561 --> 00:17:11,797
HE'S IN MY HEAD.

210
00:17:11,830 --> 00:17:14,600
HE'S IN MY HEAD!

211
00:17:14,633 --> 00:17:16,435
GET AN AMBULANCE.

212
00:17:16,468 --> 00:17:18,537
JONAS IS IN MY HEAD AGAIN.

213
00:17:18,570 --> 00:17:21,273
- OH, JONAS... - WHAT ARE YOU TALKIN' ABOUT?

214
00:17:21,306 --> 00:17:23,642
HE'S IN MY HEAD AGAIN, JOE.

215
00:17:23,675 --> 00:17:26,311
JESUS CHRIST.

216
00:17:26,345 --> 00:17:29,214
JONAS IS IN MY HEAD AGAIN.

217
00:17:29,248 --> 00:17:31,583
JONAS KELLAR IS DEAD. HE'S DEAD AND BURIED.

218
00:17:31,617 --> 00:17:34,787
HE TOLD ME. HE SAID IF I CLOSED MY EYES...

219
00:17:34,820 --> 00:17:37,389
YOU GOTTA LEAVE IT ALONE.

220
00:17:37,423 --> 00:17:39,558
I'M ALL ALONE.

221
00:17:39,591 --> 00:17:41,493
HELENE, GET IN HERE.

222
00:17:42,661 --> 00:17:45,464
HELENE, YOU CAN TAKE THE DAY OFF.

223
00:17:45,497 --> 00:17:47,666
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

224
00:18:17,796 --> 00:18:19,531
I'M DR. TOBIAS.

225
00:18:19,565 --> 00:18:21,366
I ASSUME YOU'RE WITH MR. LAZARRE.

226
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:22,768
YEAH. HE OKAY?

227
00:18:22,801 --> 00:18:26,472
HE HAS A DEEP LACERATION ON HIS LEFT FOREARM,

228
00:18:26,505 --> 00:18:28,974
SOME SELF-INFLICTED CUTS, AND HE'S LOST A LOT OF BLOOD.

229
00:18:29,007 --> 00:18:31,210
HE'S STABILIZED NOW, THOUGH.

230
00:18:31,243 --> 00:18:33,679
Woman on P.A.: DR. TOBIAS, YOU'RE WANTED IN I.C.U.

231
00:18:33,712 --> 00:18:35,514
HE WRITES HIS OWN PRESCRIPTIONS, DOESN'T HE?

232
00:18:35,547 --> 00:18:38,484
- YEAH. - IT'S NOT GOOD.

233
00:18:38,517 --> 00:18:40,719
YOUR FRIEND NEEDS HELP.

234
00:18:56,235 --> 00:18:57,870
WHAT HAPPENED?

235
00:18:57,903 --> 00:18:59,638
WELL, HE'S OKAY.

236
00:18:59,671 --> 00:19:02,207
HE GOT A LITTLE TOO DRUNK, CUT HIMSELF.

237
00:19:02,241 --> 00:19:03,642
THAT'S ALL THEY TOLD ME.

238
00:19:03,675 --> 00:19:06,478
YOU KNOW WHAT HE'S GOING TO SAY, DON'T YOU?

239
00:19:06,512 --> 00:19:07,546
HE'S GONNA SAY IT'S MY FAULT

240
00:19:07,579 --> 00:19:09,314
BECAUSE I WOULDN'T GO BACK TO HIM.

241
00:19:09,348 --> 00:19:11,650
IT'S EXACTLY WHAT HE'S GONNA SAY.

242
00:19:11,683 --> 00:19:13,952
I CAN'T TAKE ANY MORE OF THIS, JOE.

243
00:19:13,986 --> 00:19:16,989
HE EXPECTS ME TO ALWAYS BE THERE FOR HIM WHEN HE HITS THE BOTTOM,

244
00:19:17,022 --> 00:19:18,891
AND I JUST CAN'T DO IT ANYMORE.

245
00:19:32,771 --> 00:19:34,940
LOOK, TERESA, MAYBE IT'S BEST THIS HAPPENED.

246
00:19:34,973 --> 00:19:36,608
HE'LL LISTEN TO YOU THIS TIME.

247
00:19:36,642 --> 00:19:38,243
MAYBE I DON'T WANT HIM TO LISTEN.

248
00:19:38,277 --> 00:19:40,579
MAYBE I JUST WANT HIM OUT OF MY LIFE.

249
00:19:40,612 --> 00:19:42,447
WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO FIND HIM SOME HELP.

250
00:19:42,481 --> 00:19:46,018
MAYBE PUT HIM SOMEPLACE WHERE HE CAN GET BETTER.

251
00:19:46,051 --> 00:19:48,253
IF IT'S EASIER ON YOU, I'LL DRAW UP

252
00:19:48,287 --> 00:19:49,655
POWER OF ATTORNEY DOCUMENTS.

253
00:19:49,688 --> 00:19:53,425
HE'LL JUST RUN CIRCLES AROUND REHAB. WE BOTH KNOW THAT.

254
00:19:53,458 --> 00:19:55,294
THERE'S A PLACE.

255
00:19:55,327 --> 00:19:57,362
I KNOW THIS PLACE, IT'S VERY SPECIAL.

256
00:20:00,732 --> 00:20:03,268
WE'VE GOTTA HELP HIM.

257
00:20:04,603 --> 00:20:07,773
ALL RIGHT. WHATEVER YOU THINK'S BEST.

258
00:20:12,678 --> 00:20:15,447
( monitor beeping steadily )

259
00:20:28,060 --> 00:20:30,829
OH, IAN. WHAT HAVE YOU DONE NOW?

260
00:20:37,402 --> 00:20:39,638
IT CAN'T GO ON LIKE THIS.

261
00:20:39,671 --> 00:20:42,541
I CAN'T TAKE IT ANYMORE.

262
00:20:42,574 --> 00:20:44,643
I'M SORRY, HONEY.

263
00:20:44,676 --> 00:20:46,511
( inhales sharply )

264
00:20:46,545 --> 00:20:49,982
YOU HAVE TO JUST GO AND BE THE LIFE OF THE PARTY.

265
00:20:52,050 --> 00:20:55,354
LISTEN, HONEY, JOE AND I WERE TALKING,

266
00:20:55,387 --> 00:20:57,089
AND WE FOUND A PLACE FOR YOU TO GO.

267
00:20:57,122 --> 00:21:00,058
YOU KNOW, TO GET BETTER.

268
00:21:00,092 --> 00:21:03,295
AND ONCE YOU'RE BETTER, THEN...

269
00:21:08,767 --> 00:21:11,737
LISTEN, I KNOW THAT YOU'RE TIRED, SO I'M GONNA GO.

270
00:21:13,105 --> 00:21:15,574
TRY TO GET SOME REST, OKAY?

271
00:21:16,775 --> 00:21:19,611
TRY NOT TO THINK SO MUCH.

272
00:21:19,645 --> 00:21:21,813
YOU ALWAYS THINK SO MUCH.

273
00:21:31,056 --> 00:21:32,824
TERESA.

274
00:22:20,038 --> 00:22:22,808
IS THAT MR. LAZARRE? - YES. I'M JOE McNAMARA.

275
00:22:22,841 --> 00:22:24,743
I'M RACQUEL CHAMBERS, AND THIS IS JAMES.

276
00:22:24,776 --> 00:22:26,111
- JAMES. - JOE.

277
00:22:26,144 --> 00:22:27,412
THIS IS MRS. LAZARRE.

278
00:22:29,815 --> 00:22:31,717
IT LOOKS LIKE MR. LAZARRE IS A VERY LUCKY MAN

279
00:22:31,750 --> 00:22:33,919
TO HAVE A WIFE WHO CARES SO MUCH.

280
00:22:33,952 --> 00:22:35,587
- SHALL WE? - OH, LET ME.

281
00:22:35,620 --> 00:22:36,855
IT'S OKAY. I GOT IT NOW.

282
00:22:38,757 --> 00:22:41,159
WE'RE GONNA CALL YOU IN A COUPLE OF DAYS,

283
00:22:41,193 --> 00:22:42,561
AND TELL YOU HOW HE'S DOING.

284
00:22:42,594 --> 00:22:43,795
HE'S GOING TO NEED SOME TIME ALONE.

285
00:22:43,829 --> 00:22:47,532
MR. LAZARRE. I'M JAMES.

286
00:22:47,566 --> 00:22:49,434
WELCOME TO BLACKHURST.

287
00:22:49,468 --> 00:22:51,570
WE'RE GONNA GO INSIDE NOW.

288
00:22:51,603 --> 00:22:53,739
THERE'S NO VISITING FOR THE FIRST WEEK,

289
00:22:53,772 --> 00:22:55,841
THEN ONCE A WEEK FOR AN HOUR AFTER THAT.

290
00:22:55,874 --> 00:22:57,809
AND THERE WILL BE NO PHONE CALLS FOR THE FIRST THREE WEEKS.

291
00:22:57,843 --> 00:22:59,177
BYE NOW.

292
00:23:01,213 --> 00:23:02,848
THAT'S IT.

293
00:23:05,717 --> 00:23:06,885
Racquel: HELLO, MR. LAZARRE.

294
00:23:08,787 --> 00:23:11,790
DID YOU HAVE A NICE TRIP?

295
00:23:11,823 --> 00:23:14,659
YOU'RE GOING TO HAVE A WONDERFUL TIME HERE AT BLACKHURST.

296
00:23:14,693 --> 00:23:16,094
JUST RELAX.

297
00:23:16,128 --> 00:23:18,130
I FEEL LIKE WE JUST COMMITTED HIM.

298
00:23:36,915 --> 00:23:41,052
IAN, I'M GOING TO GO AND GET YOUR CHART AND THE KEY.

299
00:23:41,086 --> 00:23:42,888
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

300
00:23:44,156 --> 00:23:47,726
- YOU WON'T NEED THESE. - TAKE IT EASY.

301
00:23:47,759 --> 00:23:49,694
THIS.

302
00:23:49,728 --> 00:23:51,196
MY WATCH?

303
00:23:51,229 --> 00:23:53,465
YES, THAT GOES. AND THIS.

304
00:23:54,833 --> 00:23:56,968
AND THIS.

305
00:24:04,342 --> 00:24:05,944
JAMES.

306
00:24:08,280 --> 00:24:09,948
MY WATCH?

307
00:24:09,981 --> 00:24:13,518
WELL, IAN, SOME PATIENTS, THEY USE THE SHARP EDGES

308
00:24:13,552 --> 00:24:14,920
TO SLASH THEIR WRISTS.

309
00:24:14,953 --> 00:24:17,689
TIME'S A KILLER.

310
00:24:17,722 --> 00:24:20,959
SWISS WATCHES SEEM TO WORK THE BEST.

311
00:24:20,992 --> 00:24:23,662
- JAMES? - YES.

312
00:24:23,695 --> 00:24:26,865
HERE WE GO, IAN. YOUR NEW HOME.

313
00:24:38,810 --> 00:24:42,047
WELL, NICE AND CLEAN. NO SHARP EDGES.

314
00:24:47,586 --> 00:24:49,087
THIS ROOM NEEDS CURTAINS.

315
00:25:01,066 --> 00:25:02,167
YOUR SHOES.

316
00:25:06,071 --> 00:25:07,739
LOG HIM IN.

317
00:25:10,408 --> 00:25:12,143
HERE WE GO, IAN.

318
00:25:18,049 --> 00:25:21,186
IAN, WILL YOU GIVE ME YOUR HAND?

319
00:25:23,154 --> 00:25:25,090
THANK YOU.

320
00:25:46,745 --> 00:25:50,015
IAN, CAN YOU MAKE A FIST FOR ME?

321
00:25:51,082 --> 00:25:53,251
THANK YOU, JAMES.

322
00:26:04,162 --> 00:26:05,997
WHAT IS IT?

323
00:26:06,031 --> 00:26:07,999
YOU CAN TELL ME. I'M A DOCTOR.

324
00:26:08,033 --> 00:26:10,769
I LIKE DOCTORS.

325
00:26:15,740 --> 00:26:17,676
HOW LONG HAVE YOU BEEN A NURSE?

326
00:26:17,709 --> 00:26:20,345
OH, I'M NOT A NURSE.

327
00:26:20,378 --> 00:26:23,014
I JUST LIKE WEARING THE UNIFORM.

328
00:26:24,816 --> 00:26:26,051
ALL RIGHT.

329
00:26:31,056 --> 00:26:32,123
THERE.

330
00:26:32,157 --> 00:26:34,726
NOW YOU JUST RELAX.

331
00:26:34,759 --> 00:26:37,329
IT'S ONLY A SEDATIVE.

332
00:26:39,064 --> 00:26:41,333
DIAZEPAM?

333
00:26:41,366 --> 00:26:43,335
PROMAZINE?

334
00:26:43,368 --> 00:26:45,170
MORPHINE?

335
00:26:45,203 --> 00:26:48,173
- SHH. - I'D LIKE SOME MORPHINE.

336
00:26:51,142 --> 00:26:52,711
SH.

337
00:26:54,012 --> 00:26:56,181
I'M SCARED.

338
00:28:17,162 --> 00:28:20,265
LET ME OUTTA HERE!

339
00:28:21,399 --> 00:28:24,836
LET ME OUT OF HERE!!

340
00:28:26,538 --> 00:28:30,141
OH, LET ME OUT OF HERE!

341
00:28:31,276 --> 00:28:34,312
PLEASE LET ME OUT OF HERE!

342
00:28:37,348 --> 00:28:40,251
LET ME OUT OF HERE!

343
00:28:48,893 --> 00:28:50,462
TAKE THESE OFF.

344
00:28:50,495 --> 00:28:53,098
NOW JUST TAKE IT EASY, SWEETIE.

345
00:28:53,131 --> 00:28:56,000
YOU'RE OVER THE WORST OF IT. YOU GAVE US A SCARE, THOUGH.

346
00:28:56,034 --> 00:28:58,236
WE DIDN'T THINK YOU WERE GOING TO MAKE IT.

347
00:28:58,269 --> 00:29:00,572
WHO AUTHORIZED RESTRAINING?

348
00:29:00,605 --> 00:29:04,242
YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED TO RESTRAIN PATIENTS IN DETOX.

349
00:29:04,275 --> 00:29:06,244
I COULD'VE BEEN ASPHYXIATED.

350
00:29:06,277 --> 00:29:08,213
LISTEN TO ME. IT TOOK SIX MEN

351
00:29:08,246 --> 00:29:11,116
JUST TO KEEP YOU FROM TEARING OUT YOUR OWN STITCHES.

352
00:29:11,149 --> 00:29:13,051
ARE YOU READY TO GET UP?

353
00:29:13,084 --> 00:29:15,487
DOCTOR WANTS TO SEE YOU SOON.

354
00:29:15,520 --> 00:29:17,889
COME ON, IAN, LET'S GO.

355
00:29:17,922 --> 00:29:19,924
- HOW LONG HAVE I BEEN ASLEEP? - THREE DAYS. COME ON.

356
00:29:19,958 --> 00:29:22,127
- UP WE GO. - THREE DAYS?

357
00:29:24,162 --> 00:29:26,197
WHAT IS IT?

358
00:29:37,609 --> 00:29:39,844
THOSE ARE NASTY.

359
00:29:46,951 --> 00:29:49,020
IAN, YOU WERE CONVULSING,

360
00:29:49,053 --> 00:29:51,623
AND THE DOCTOR TOLD US TO TIE YOU DOWN.

361
00:29:51,656 --> 00:29:53,491
WHO'S IN CHARGE HERE?

362
00:29:53,525 --> 00:29:57,028
- IAN, JUST CALM DOWN. - WHO'S THE DOCTOR?

363
00:29:57,061 --> 00:29:59,197
DR. RENQUIST IS YOUR DOCTOR,

364
00:29:59,230 --> 00:30:01,299
AND YOU'RE GOING TO SEE HIM SOON. THEY ALL DO EVENTUALLY.

365
00:30:01,332 --> 00:30:03,501
THE VERNON RENQUIST?

366
00:30:05,403 --> 00:30:08,006
THERE. ALL BETTER.

367
00:30:09,374 --> 00:30:13,545
IAN, YOUR WIFE, SHE'S VERY PRETTY.

368
00:30:15,547 --> 00:30:18,082
MY WIFE'S DEAD.

369
00:30:18,116 --> 00:30:20,385
THERE. THAT'S BETTER, ISN'T IT?

370
00:30:20,418 --> 00:30:23,254
JAMES IS GONNA TAKE YOU TO THE CAFETERIA,

371
00:30:23,288 --> 00:30:24,622
AND YOU'RE GOING TO EAT SOMETHING.

372
00:30:24,656 --> 00:30:26,558
I WILL SEE YOU LATER.

373
00:31:01,059 --> 00:31:02,694
WHAT ARE YOU IN FOR?

374
00:31:05,263 --> 00:31:08,633
SORRY. BAD JOKE. WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

375
00:31:14,973 --> 00:31:18,176
IT'S A VERY NICE DAY, ISN'T IT?

376
00:31:23,047 --> 00:31:24,949
HOW LONG HAVE YOU BEEN HERE?

377
00:31:26,251 --> 00:31:27,752
TWENTY WEEKS.

378
00:31:27,785 --> 00:31:31,222
TWENTY WEEKS. THAT'S A LONG TIME FOR DETOX.

379
00:31:31,256 --> 00:31:33,491
WHAT KIND OF THERAPY...

380
00:31:33,524 --> 00:31:37,629
ARE YOU DOING? INDIVIDUAL OR GROUP?

381
00:31:40,331 --> 00:31:41,666
WHAT HAVE THEY GOT YOU ON?

382
00:31:41,699 --> 00:31:43,735
PROZAC OR RITALIN?

383
00:32:01,452 --> 00:32:06,057
DOC, THE RULES ARE, YOU GOTTA EAT.

384
00:32:12,597 --> 00:32:14,365
YOU SAYIN' YOU'RE NOT GONNA EAT?

385
00:32:14,399 --> 00:32:16,134
OW. THAT HURTS.

386
00:32:18,369 --> 00:32:21,105
- WHAT ARE YOU DOIN'? - COME ON WITH ME.

387
00:32:21,139 --> 00:32:22,440
WHO'S YOUR SUPERVISOR?

388
00:33:20,264 --> 00:33:22,300
( keys jingling )

389
00:33:27,438 --> 00:33:30,041
ARE YA HUNGRY?

390
00:33:35,646 --> 00:33:37,482
YEAH.

391
00:33:41,886 --> 00:33:43,821
STAY RIGHT THERE.

392
00:33:46,591 --> 00:33:49,127
( thunder rumbling )

393
00:33:55,933 --> 00:33:58,603
WENDY, WENDY.

394
00:34:05,209 --> 00:34:08,379
I THOUGHT YOU WOULD BE NEEDING THIS ABOUT NOW.

395
00:34:08,413 --> 00:34:10,181
THANK YOU.

396
00:34:11,883 --> 00:34:14,318
HE'S VERY STRONG.

397
00:34:17,355 --> 00:34:19,624
HOW MUCH SEDATIVE DID HE SEE YOU ADMINISTER?

398
00:34:19,657 --> 00:34:22,560
IT WAS 25 MILLIGRAMS OR SO.

399
00:34:22,593 --> 00:34:27,098
HE THOUGHT IT WAS CHLORPROMAZINE OR SOMETHING.

400
00:34:28,666 --> 00:34:31,469
DID YOU TELL HIM WHAT IT REALLY WAS?

401
00:34:31,502 --> 00:34:32,737
NO.

402
00:34:37,375 --> 00:34:38,676
WENDY.

403
00:34:38,709 --> 00:34:40,945
HE KEEPS CALLING FOR WENDY.

404
00:34:40,978 --> 00:34:43,948
- WHO IS SHE? - HIS FIRST WIFE.

405
00:34:43,981 --> 00:34:47,485
TRAGICALLY KILLED IN A D.U.I. ACCIDENT.

406
00:34:47,518 --> 00:34:50,688
HE MUST HAVE LOVED HER VERY MUCH.

407
00:34:50,721 --> 00:34:53,291
APPARENTLY SO.

408
00:35:01,332 --> 00:35:04,168
YOU KNOW, I THINK HE'S BEGINNING TO LIKE YOU.

409
00:35:04,202 --> 00:35:07,572
WON'T BE LONG NOW BEFORE YOU'RE PART OF HIS DREAMS.

410
00:35:11,876 --> 00:35:14,412
ISN'T IT TIME THAT YOU TOLD HIM?

411
00:35:14,445 --> 00:35:18,382
TOLD HIM WHAT? THAT HIS DREAMS AREN'T REAL?

412
00:35:18,416 --> 00:35:20,251
THAT'S HIS ONLY LINK TO SANITY.

413
00:35:20,284 --> 00:35:22,386
IF HE KNEW WHAT WAS IN THAT SYRINGE,

414
00:35:22,420 --> 00:35:24,655
HIS WHOLE WORLD WOULD COLLAPSE.

415
00:35:24,689 --> 00:35:26,591
HE'D REMEMBER TO LIE.

416
00:35:26,624 --> 00:35:29,327
WE'D LOSE HIM, HE'D BE GONE.

417
00:35:29,360 --> 00:35:31,529
NO.

418
00:35:31,562 --> 00:35:35,500
LET HIM KNOW THAT YOU'RE UPPING THE DOSAGE.

419
00:35:35,533 --> 00:35:37,568
ALL RIGHT.

420
00:35:40,571 --> 00:35:42,640
WHAT DO YOU THINK WILL BECOME OF HIM?

421
00:35:42,673 --> 00:35:45,009
I DON'T KNOW.

422
00:35:45,042 --> 00:35:47,612
HE SEEMS TO BE SEEKING SOME KIND OF TRUTH

423
00:35:47,645 --> 00:35:49,614
IN HIS HEAD.

424
00:35:49,647 --> 00:35:52,950
HE MAY BE CLOSE TO AN ANSWER.

425
00:35:52,984 --> 00:35:55,586
I JUST DON'T KNOW WHAT KIND OF PEACE HE'S GONNA FIND

426
00:35:55,620 --> 00:35:58,556
WHEN HE FINALLY GETS THERE, IF EVER.

427
00:36:03,628 --> 00:36:05,596
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

428
00:36:12,870 --> 00:36:15,239
( thunder rumbling )

429
00:36:17,742 --> 00:36:21,445
( phone ringing )

430
00:36:29,453 --> 00:36:32,723
( ringing continues )

431
00:36:32,757 --> 00:36:37,595
IAN, IT'S FOR YOU. IT'S YOUR WIFE.

432
00:36:52,343 --> 00:36:54,512
CAN YOU IDENTIFY THE BODY, SIR?

433
00:36:54,545 --> 00:36:57,748
WHY ASK HIM? BODY'S BURNT BEYOND RECOGNITION.

434
00:36:57,782 --> 00:36:59,050
EVEN THE CORONER HAD A DIFFICULT TIME

435
00:36:59,083 --> 00:37:01,619
MATCHING UP THE DENTAL RECORDS.

436
00:37:01,652 --> 00:37:06,257
- MR. LAZARRE? - YOU OKAY TO DRIVE, DOCTOR?

437
00:37:07,992 --> 00:37:09,560
DOCTOR?

438
00:37:10,661 --> 00:37:13,564
( water running in toilet )

439
00:37:46,797 --> 00:37:47,965
HEY!

440
00:38:06,117 --> 00:38:08,085
HEY, THIS AREA'S OFF LIMITS.

441
00:38:08,119 --> 00:38:10,621
- I WANNA USE THE TELEPHONE. - COME WITH ME!

442
00:38:10,655 --> 00:38:12,723
- GET YOUR HANDS OFF ME! - COME ON!

443
00:38:12,757 --> 00:38:14,125
LET GO OF ME!

444
00:38:14,158 --> 00:38:16,727
WHAT SEEMS TO BE THE PROBLEM?

445
00:38:16,761 --> 00:38:18,696
DR. RENQUIST.

446
00:38:18,729 --> 00:38:20,798
YES,

447
00:38:20,831 --> 00:38:23,434
I JUST WANTED TO MAKE A CALL.

448
00:38:28,105 --> 00:38:31,542
I JUST WANTED TO CALL SOMEBODY.

449
00:38:31,575 --> 00:38:34,779
YOU WANT TO LEAVE US, DON'T YOU?

450
00:38:34,812 --> 00:38:36,814
NO.

451
00:38:36,847 --> 00:38:39,050
I JUST WANNA CALL SOMEONE.

452
00:38:39,083 --> 00:38:42,787
WELL, THERE'S A TELEPHONE.

453
00:38:42,820 --> 00:38:44,955
YOU WANT TO USE IT? GO AHEAD. USE IT.

454
00:38:44,989 --> 00:38:47,591
GO AHEAD.

455
00:38:50,995 --> 00:38:54,899
- GO AHEAD. - I UNDERSTAND WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

456
00:38:54,932 --> 00:38:59,070
IT'S REVERSE PSYCHOLOGY 101.

457
00:38:59,103 --> 00:39:02,039
GO AHEAD. USE THE TELEPHONE.

458
00:39:21,926 --> 00:39:25,529
STEP OUT OF LINE, AND WE PUNISH YOU. IT'S VERY SIMPLE.

459
00:39:25,563 --> 00:39:28,499
WE HAVE A "THREE STRIKES, YOU'RE OUT" RULE, IAN.

460
00:39:28,532 --> 00:39:31,736
ONLY HERE, OUT MEANS IN.

461
00:39:31,769 --> 00:39:33,771
YOU STAY IN FOR AS LONG AS IT TAKES.

462
00:39:33,804 --> 00:39:35,506
DO I MAKE MYSELF CLEAR?

463
00:39:35,539 --> 00:39:37,775
THIS ISN'T REHAB.

464
00:39:37,808 --> 00:39:39,910
YOU DON'T HAVE THE RIGHT TO COMMIT ME.

465
00:39:42,480 --> 00:39:43,848
REALLY?

466
00:39:45,015 --> 00:39:47,051
I'LL HAVE TO SEE ABOUT THAT.

467
00:39:47,084 --> 00:39:50,654
James: IT'S OKAY. IT'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.

468
00:40:28,559 --> 00:40:30,861
GOOD EVENING. CAN I GET YOU A DRINK BEFORE DINNER?

469
00:40:32,062 --> 00:40:34,799
COFFEE.

470
00:40:34,832 --> 00:40:36,534
SAME FOR ME.

471
00:40:38,035 --> 00:40:40,838
SO HAVE YOU TALKED TO IAN? IT'S BEEN A WEEK.

472
00:40:40,871 --> 00:40:42,206
I'M SURE HE'S FINE.

473
00:40:42,239 --> 00:40:44,175
HE'S A FIGHTER. HE'LL MAKE IT.

474
00:40:44,208 --> 00:40:46,710
IF HE DOESN'T...

475
00:40:46,744 --> 00:40:49,914
WHAT DO YOU MEAN, IF HE DOESN'T?

476
00:40:49,947 --> 00:40:51,882
I DIDN'T WANNA UPSET YOU,

477
00:40:51,916 --> 00:40:53,851
BUT I THINK YOU OUGHTA KNOW.

478
00:40:53,884 --> 00:40:55,986
I GOT A CALL FROM IAN'S DOCTOR, DR. RENQUIST.

479
00:40:56,020 --> 00:40:58,322
HIS RECOVERY'S NOT GOING VERY WELL.

480
00:40:58,355 --> 00:41:01,659
- APPARENTLY, THERE'S SOME PROBLEMS. - WHAT KIND OF PROBLEMS?

481
00:41:01,692 --> 00:41:03,961
NOTHING SERIOUS. NOT YET. IT'S JUST...

482
00:41:03,994 --> 00:41:06,997
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT? JUST SPIT IT OUT.

483
