01:02:13,129 --> 01:02:15,398
LITTLE FOOTSIES IN HERE.

727
01:02:15,431 --> 01:02:17,967
HUH? LET ME SEE.

728
01:02:18,000 --> 01:02:20,269
IT'S ALL RIGHT, IT'S OKAY.

729
01:02:20,303 --> 01:02:21,571
THERE'S A WHOLE LOT GOIN' ON

730
01:02:21,604 --> 01:02:24,006
IN THAT LITTLE BITTY MIND OF HIS.

731
01:02:24,040 --> 01:02:26,142
JAMES, THAT'S ENOUGH NOW.

732
01:02:26,175 --> 01:02:27,376
OKAY.

733
01:02:32,048 --> 01:02:34,150
EVERYTHING'S GONNA BE OKAY.

734
01:02:34,183 --> 01:02:37,320
YOU'RE GONNA GET BETTER SOON.

735
01:02:39,322 --> 01:02:41,290
YES, YOU WILL.

736
01:02:41,324 --> 01:02:43,292
YES, YOU'LL SEE.

737
01:02:45,361 --> 01:02:47,396
YOU TRUST ME.

738
01:02:48,931 --> 01:02:50,900
TRUST ME.

739
01:03:04,347 --> 01:03:07,083
DOCTOR, I DON'T THINK THAT'S APPROPRIATE.

740
01:03:12,221 --> 01:03:14,257
NOW, NIGHTY-NIGHT.

741
01:03:55,998 --> 01:03:57,466
JOE, IT'S TERESA.

742
01:03:57,500 --> 01:03:59,569
I MEAN, MRS. LAZARRE HERE TO SEE YOU.

743
01:03:59,602 --> 01:04:01,404
SEND HER IN.

744
01:04:02,705 --> 01:04:05,341
HI. THIS WAS A SURPRISE.

745
01:04:06,742 --> 01:04:09,579
- JOE, LISTEN, WE NEED TO TALK. - WHAT'S THE MATTER?

746
01:04:09,612 --> 01:04:12,348
IT'S ABOUT IAN. I NEED TO SEE HIM AGAIN.

747
01:04:12,381 --> 01:04:14,517
YOU SURE THAT'S A GOOD IDEA?

748
01:04:14,550 --> 01:04:17,153
YOU KNOW HOW FRAGILE HE IS.

749
01:04:17,186 --> 01:04:19,522
SOMETHING IS NOT RIGHT. I KNOW HIM.

750
01:04:19,555 --> 01:04:21,457
HE WOULDN'T GET LIKE THIS.

751
01:04:21,490 --> 01:04:24,360
LOOK, TERESA, YOU'RE NOT BEING VERY OBJECTIVE.

752
01:04:24,393 --> 01:04:27,230
DID YOU MEAN WHAT YOU SAID ABOUT THE POWER OF ATTORNEY?

753
01:04:27,263 --> 01:04:29,398
ABOUT TAKING THE TREATMENT TO THE SECOND LEVEL?

754
01:04:29,432 --> 01:04:32,068
LOOK, I DON'T WANNA DO THAT ANY MORE THAN YOU DO, BUT...

755
01:04:32,101 --> 01:04:34,370
BUT?

756
01:04:36,172 --> 01:04:38,407
LOOK, WHY DON'T WE TALK ABOUT IT TONIGHT?

757
01:04:38,441 --> 01:04:39,475
I'LL COME OVER, OKAY?

758
01:04:39,508 --> 01:04:42,278
FINE. I NEED TO SEE HIM.

759
01:04:42,311 --> 01:04:44,180
YOU WILL, YOU WILL. WE'LL TALK ABOUT IT OVER DINNER.

760
01:04:44,213 --> 01:04:45,548
OKAY.

761
01:05:05,301 --> 01:05:07,470
JAMES, WOULD YOU GIVE US A SECOND, PLEASE?

762
01:05:07,503 --> 01:05:09,272
ARE YOU SURE?

763
01:05:09,305 --> 01:05:12,074
LOOK AT HIM. HE'S NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

764
01:05:18,648 --> 01:05:20,416
IT'S OKAY.

765
01:05:24,420 --> 01:05:26,355
WHERE DID RENQUIST FIND YOU?

766
01:05:26,389 --> 01:05:27,990
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

767
01:05:32,161 --> 01:05:34,030
ON THE STRIP?

768
01:05:34,063 --> 01:05:37,266
TURNING TRICKS FOR A FIX.

769
01:05:39,535 --> 01:05:41,504
IT'S OKAY.

770
01:05:43,372 --> 01:05:45,675
IAN, I DON'T KNOW WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

771
01:05:50,346 --> 01:05:54,650
YOU'RE NOT EVEN A CERTIFIED NURSE, ARE YOU?

772
01:05:54,684 --> 01:05:57,420
ARE YOU?

773
01:05:58,754 --> 01:06:00,623
IAN, LET US HELP YOU.

774
01:06:02,491 --> 01:06:06,495
IF YOU WANNA HELP ME, YOU'LL HELP ME GET OUTTA HERE.

775
01:06:07,730 --> 01:06:11,233
James: DINNERTIME. ARE YOU READY?

776
01:06:15,571 --> 01:06:17,473
HOPE YOU'RE HUNGRY.

777
01:07:56,439 --> 01:08:00,509
( phone ringing )

778
01:08:06,348 --> 01:08:08,217
HELLO.

779
01:08:09,652 --> 01:08:11,520
HELLO?

780
01:08:16,292 --> 01:08:18,194
WHO WAS IT?

781
01:08:18,227 --> 01:08:21,564
I DON'T KNOW. PROBABLY A WRONG NUMBER.

782
01:08:30,539 --> 01:08:34,243
UM, LISTEN, I HAVE AN EARLY DAY TOMORROW.

783
01:08:34,276 --> 01:08:36,679
ALL RIGHT.

784
01:08:36,712 --> 01:08:40,349
I JUST NEED TO GO OVER SOME POWER OF ATTORNEY DOCUMENTS FOR IAN.

785
01:08:47,790 --> 01:08:50,459
- JOE, WHAT ARE YOU DOING? - COME ON, COME ON.

786
01:08:52,962 --> 01:08:54,530
( phone ringing )

787
01:08:54,563 --> 01:08:56,665
WHY DON'T YOU LET ME GET THIS?

788
01:08:58,667 --> 01:09:01,203
- HELLO. - JOE?

789
01:09:06,442 --> 01:09:08,544
WHO WAS IT?

790
01:09:08,577 --> 01:09:10,713
OH, NOBODY. JUST A PRANK CALL.

791
01:09:20,689 --> 01:09:21,724
STRIKE THREE, IAN.

792
01:09:27,863 --> 01:09:30,266
LET ME OUTTA HERE!

793
01:09:30,299 --> 01:09:32,735
YOU'RE SO CLOSE TO THE TRUTH.

794
01:09:32,768 --> 01:09:35,271
YOU HAVE NO IDEA.

795
01:09:42,545 --> 01:09:43,946
( truck horn blares )

796
01:10:07,469 --> 01:10:09,705
JESUS CHRIST, LADY.

797
01:10:09,738 --> 01:10:11,840
YOU OKAY?

798
01:10:13,442 --> 01:10:15,945
YEAH, I'M FINE. SORRY.

799
01:11:08,697 --> 01:11:11,367
I'M SORRY THAT YOU HAVE TO SEE HIM LIKE THIS.

800
01:11:11,400 --> 01:11:13,035
OH, MY GOD, IAN.

801
01:11:25,748 --> 01:11:28,083
- POOR GUY. - ( silence )

802
01:11:31,520 --> 01:11:33,022
TERESA!

803
01:11:33,055 --> 01:11:36,825
HE'S FIGHTING SOME KIND OF BATTLE IN HIS HEAD.

804
01:11:36,859 --> 01:11:39,128
SOMETHING TO DO WITH THE DEATH OF HIS FIRST WIFE.

805
01:11:39,161 --> 01:11:40,763
WENDY?

806
01:11:40,796 --> 01:11:43,632
SHE WAS DRUNK. SHE DROVE HERSELF OFF THE ROAD.

807
01:11:43,666 --> 01:11:44,767
IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.

808
01:11:44,800 --> 01:11:46,568
WELL, NOT IN YOUR HUSBAND'S MIND.

809
01:11:46,602 --> 01:11:48,504
TERESA!!

810
01:11:48,537 --> 01:11:50,739
HE'S SO AFRAID OF REALITY

811
01:11:50,773 --> 01:11:53,542
THAT HE'S CONSTRUCTED A WHOLE PARADOXICAL DREAM WORLD

812
01:11:53,575 --> 01:11:55,711
WHERE HE CAN PLAY OUT THE PAST.

813
01:11:55,744 --> 01:11:58,147
IN OTHER WORDS, IT'S HOPELESS.

814
01:11:58,180 --> 01:12:00,049
TERESA, PLEASE!

815
01:12:00,082 --> 01:12:02,985
I DON'T KNOW, MR. McNAMARA.

816
01:12:03,018 --> 01:12:04,586
I REALLY DON'T KNOW.

817
01:12:04,620 --> 01:12:07,856
I'VE BEEN TREATING PATIENTS LIKE THIS FOR OVER 30 YEARS.

818
01:12:07,890 --> 01:12:10,159
I STILL DON'T HAVE THE SLIGHTEST REASONABLE ANSWER.

819
01:12:10,192 --> 01:12:13,762
HE'S FIGHTING THE TREATMENT.

820
01:12:13,796 --> 01:12:16,799
HE'S FIGHTING FOR HIS LIFE.

821
01:12:19,835 --> 01:12:22,471
- I'VE SEEN ENOUGH. - YOU OKAY?

822
01:12:22,504 --> 01:12:25,174
YEAH. I'M FINE.

823
01:12:25,207 --> 01:12:26,742
TERESA!

824
01:12:26,775 --> 01:12:30,479
I CAN'T HELP YOU.

825
01:12:30,512 --> 01:12:32,848
I CAN'T HELP YOU.

826
01:12:34,817 --> 01:12:36,652
I'LL BE OUT IN A MINUTE.

827
01:12:43,125 --> 01:12:45,527
I CAN'T HELP YOU, TERESA.

828
01:13:15,557 --> 01:13:17,726
IAN.

829
01:13:20,662 --> 01:13:23,766
IAN, GET INTO BED NOW. NOW, GET IN THERE.

830
01:13:37,780 --> 01:13:40,482
COME ON. WHAT'S IN THERE?

831
01:13:40,516 --> 01:13:43,285
WHAT'S IN THAT HEAD OF YOURS?

832
01:13:43,318 --> 01:13:45,754
LET ME OUTTA HERE, RENQUIST!

833
01:13:46,889 --> 01:13:48,891
LET ME OUTTA HERE!

834
01:13:48,924 --> 01:13:51,960
LET ME OUT OF HERE!!

835
01:13:51,994 --> 01:13:55,898
( Ian's voice echoing )

836
01:13:58,667 --> 01:14:00,969
( wordless scream )

837
01:14:01,003 --> 01:14:03,205
LET ME OUT OF HERE!

838
01:14:03,238 --> 01:14:06,141
LET ME OUTTA HERE!

839
01:14:06,175 --> 01:14:09,912
RENQUIST, LET ME OUT OF HERE!

840
01:14:26,995 --> 01:14:28,630
WENDY.

841
01:14:33,769 --> 01:14:35,571
WENDY.

842
01:14:35,604 --> 01:14:38,540
YOUR WIFE WAS HERE TODAY.

843
01:14:38,574 --> 01:14:41,276
WENDY.

844
01:14:41,310 --> 01:14:43,946
YES, JUST TAKE IT EASY.

845
01:14:47,015 --> 01:14:50,018
WENDY'S DEAD.

846
01:14:50,052 --> 01:14:53,222
NOW, IAN, JUST TELL ME WHAT YOU SEE.

847
01:15:05,000 --> 01:15:07,703
WELCOME TO NOWHERE.

848
01:15:07,736 --> 01:15:11,006
I WANNA KNOW THE TRUTH.

849
01:15:11,039 --> 01:15:13,909
I THOUGHT YOU CHANGED YOUR MIND.

850
01:15:18,780 --> 01:15:21,016
CAN'T YOU SHOW ME?

851
01:15:25,053 --> 01:15:28,023
WHEN THINGS GET BLACKEST,

852
01:15:28,056 --> 01:15:30,759
AND YOU DON'T KNOW WHERE TO TURN...

853
01:15:34,429 --> 01:15:38,600
REMEMBER, WHEN YOU CLOSE YOUR EYES,

854
01:15:40,802 --> 01:15:43,105
ALL YOU HAVE IS YOURSELF.

855
01:15:47,042 --> 01:15:49,778
ALL YOU HAVE IS YOURSELF.

856
01:15:52,014 --> 01:15:54,683
ALL YOU HAVE IS YOURSELF.

857
01:15:56,785 --> 01:15:58,854
ALL YOU HAVE IS YOURSELF.

858
01:16:55,410 --> 01:16:58,814
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING? - DON'T ASK, DON'T ASK.

859
01:16:58,847 --> 01:17:00,882
- ARE YOU ALL RIGHT? - YEAH.

860
01:17:00,916 --> 01:17:03,051
I ALMOST GOT MYSELF KILLED.

861
01:17:03,085 --> 01:17:05,253
I RAN INTO THE TRUCK.

862
01:17:05,287 --> 01:17:07,489
I MEAN, I ALMOST RAN INTO THE TRUCK.

863
01:17:07,522 --> 01:17:10,192
I THINK I HAD TOO MUCH CHAMPAGNE.

864
01:17:10,225 --> 01:17:12,894
- I KNOW. - ( both laughing )

865
01:17:23,138 --> 01:17:33,048
BIT OF A RUSH, ISN'T IT?

866
01:17:33,081 --> 01:17:35,217
NO.

867
01:17:35,250 --> 01:17:37,419
NO. JOE!

868
01:17:37,452 --> 01:17:39,154
DON'T!

869
01:17:39,187 --> 01:17:41,123
NO.

870
01:17:41,156 --> 01:17:43,358
JOE. DON'T.

871
01:17:43,392 --> 01:17:45,394
STOP. JOE, DON'T!

872
01:17:45,427 --> 01:17:47,162
( screams ) JOE, DON'T!

873
01:17:47,195 --> 01:17:48,497
OH, NO, NO.

874
01:17:48,530 --> 01:17:52,134
( screaming )

875
01:17:56,171 --> 01:17:57,305
LOOK AT IT.

876
01:17:57,339 --> 01:17:58,707
- NO! - ( bones snapping )

877
01:18:18,026 --> 01:18:19,928
LOOK AT IT.

878
01:18:44,453 --> 01:18:46,154
LOOK AT IT.

879
01:18:58,266 --> 01:19:00,035
OH, NO.

880
01:19:09,111 --> 01:19:11,079
WENDY.

881
01:19:13,615 --> 01:19:15,517
WENDY.

882
01:19:18,553 --> 01:19:20,455
I'M SORRY.

883
01:19:20,489 --> 01:19:22,591
I'M SORRY.

884
01:19:27,629 --> 01:19:29,498
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

885
01:19:43,979 --> 01:19:46,548
DON'T TELL ME THIS IS ONE OF MY DREAMS.

886
01:19:47,582 --> 01:19:49,217
IAN, YOU PUT THAT NEEDLE DOWN.

887
01:19:49,251 --> 01:19:52,454
THIS ISN'T GONNA SOLVE ANYTHING.

888
01:19:53,522 --> 01:19:55,857
THIS ISN'T ONE OF MY DREAMS, IS IT?

889
01:19:55,891 --> 01:19:57,659
NO.

890
01:19:57,692 --> 01:20:00,028
THEN GIVE ME THE KEYS.

891
01:20:25,253 --> 01:20:26,655
James: SHIT.

892
01:20:31,459 --> 01:20:34,196
ORDERLY.

893
01:20:34,229 --> 01:20:35,964
ORDERLY!

894
01:20:36,965 --> 01:20:39,134
OPEN IT!

895
01:20:42,504 --> 01:20:44,239
OPEN THE DOOR!

896
01:20:44,272 --> 01:20:46,708
( pounding continues )

897
01:20:46,741 --> 01:20:50,178
POOR GUY HAVIN' NIGHTMARES AGAIN, HUH?

898
01:20:50,212 --> 01:20:53,415
WHY BOTHER? THAT MOTHERFUCKER IS CRAZY.

899
01:20:53,448 --> 01:20:55,584
LET HIM ROT WITH THE REST OF 'EM.

900
01:20:55,617 --> 01:20:57,319
COME ON.

901
01:20:57,352 --> 01:21:00,322
ORDERLY! OPEN THE DOOR!

902
01:21:00,355 --> 01:21:03,191
LET'S GO OUT THERE!

903
01:21:21,309 --> 01:21:23,278
GEEZ, IAN.

904
01:21:23,311 --> 01:21:25,180
WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU DOING HERE?

905
01:21:26,514 --> 01:21:29,351
I DON'T KNOW WHAT YOU'VE BEEN GIVING ME.

906
01:21:29,384 --> 01:21:31,519
A NEUROLEPTIC?

907
01:21:31,553 --> 01:21:33,388
AN ANTI-PSYCHOTIC?

908
01:21:33,421 --> 01:21:36,358
BUT YOU'RE GOING TO GET ME OUT OF HERE.

909
01:21:36,391 --> 01:21:40,128
IAN, LOOK, JUST GO BACK TO YOUR ROOM. IT'S ALL RIGHT.

910
01:21:40,161 --> 01:21:42,397
YOU'VE BEEN MAKING REAL PROGRESS.

911
01:21:42,430 --> 01:21:44,399
YOU DON'T WANT TO RUIN EVERYTHING NOW.

912
01:21:44,432 --> 01:21:46,401
I THOUGHT PERHAPS YOUR TREATMENT

913
01:21:46,434 --> 01:21:48,670
WAS GONNA BRING ME THROUGH A DEPRESSION, AN OBSESSION.

914
01:21:48,703 --> 01:21:52,340
BUT THE NIGHTMARES MADE IT CLEAR.

915
01:21:52,374 --> 01:21:54,476
IAN, DON'T YOU SEE WHAT'S HAPPENED?

916
01:21:54,509 --> 01:21:56,344
YOU'VE BECOME PARANOID, DELUSIONAL.

917
01:21:56,378 --> 01:21:58,213
YOU THINK EVERYBODY'S AGAINST YOU.

918
01:21:58,246 --> 01:22:00,482
THE DRUG DIDN'T CAUSE YOUR NIGHTMARES.

919
01:22:00,515 --> 01:22:02,417
YOU YOURSELF DID.

920
01:22:02,450 --> 01:22:05,387
LOOK, THE SO-CALLED DRUG IS JUST A CATALYST.

921
01:22:07,255 --> 01:22:12,427
JOSEPH McNAMARA IS CRIMINALLY INSANE.

922
01:22:12,460 --> 01:22:15,163
HE'S GOT PATHOLOGICAL ENVY.

923
01:22:15,196 --> 01:22:18,466
HE'S... HE'S GOT A VENDETTA AGAINST ME.

924
01:22:18,500 --> 01:22:20,268
WHAT YOU'RE DOING IS UTTERLY HOPELESS.

925
01:22:20,302 --> 01:22:23,138
HE COMMITTED MURDER, AND HE RAPED MY WIFE.

926
01:22:30,345 --> 01:22:33,081
CALL SOMEBODY FOR MY LUGGAGE.

927
01:22:33,114 --> 01:22:35,317
I'M CHECKING OUT.

928
01:22:35,350 --> 01:22:37,319
OPEN IT UP.

929
01:22:37,352 --> 01:22:40,388
ORDERLY, OPEN THE DOOR!

930
01:22:50,332 --> 01:22:53,435
GO AND CALL SECURITY.

931
01:22:53,468 --> 01:22:55,770
WAIT A MINUTE. DON'T YOU HURT HIM.

932
01:22:55,804 --> 01:22:58,807
- HE PUT HIS HANDS ON YOU. - DON'T HURT HIM.

933
01:23:02,177 --> 01:23:04,312
STOP THIS NONSENSE, IAN.

934
01:23:04,346 --> 01:23:06,247
YOU'RE A SICK MAN. LET ME HELP YOU.

935
01:23:06,281 --> 01:23:07,549
ALL THIS TIME, I NEVER KNEW

936
01:23:07,582 --> 01:23:09,517
IF I WAS DREAMIN' OR I WAS AWAKE.

937
01:23:09,551 --> 01:23:12,087
JUST THINK, I COULD BE DREAMIN' RIGHT NOW.

938
01:23:12,120 --> 01:23:14,289
TAKE IT EASY, IAN. THIS IS NO DREAM.

939
01:23:14,322 --> 01:23:16,157
NO, IT'S A FUCKIN' NIGHTMARE.

940
01:23:16,191 --> 01:23:18,360
JOE PLAYED US ALL LIKE A HARP.

941
01:23:18,393 --> 01:23:20,228
YOU'RE DELIRIOUS. PLEASE, IAN.

942
01:23:20,261 --> 01:23:21,696
I NEVER FELT BETTER IN MY LIFE.

943
01:23:21,730 --> 01:23:23,531
( security alarm blaring )

944
01:23:23,565 --> 01:23:25,700
GET ME OUTTA HERE,

945
01:23:25,734 --> 01:23:29,404
OR I'M GONNA GIVE YOU...

946
01:23:29,437 --> 01:23:33,475
Woman on P.A.: DR. RENQUIST, PLEASE REPORT TO SECURITY IMMEDIATELY.

947
01:23:33,508 --> 01:23:40,415
DR. RENQUIST, PLEASE REPORT TO SECURITY IMMEDIATELY.

948
01:23:40,448 --> 01:23:44,819
DR. RENQUIST, PLEASE REPORT TO SECURITY IMMEDIATELY.

949
01:23:47,922 --> 01:23:50,458
I'LL DO IT!

950
01:23:50,492 --> 01:23:54,329
- Racquel: IAN, STOP. - I'LL FILL HIM FULL OF THIS SHIT.

951
01:23:54,362 --> 01:23:56,431
- NO, IAN. - GO AHEAD, IAN.

952
01:23:56,464 --> 01:23:59,601
GO AHEAD. IT'S ONLY A NORMAL SALINE SOLUTION.

953
01:23:59,634 --> 01:24:02,137
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

954
01:24:02,170 --> 01:24:04,272
THAT'S ALL IT EVER WAS.

955
01:24:04,305 --> 01:24:05,874
EVERYTHING YOU'VE BEEN THROUGH, EVERYTHING,

956
01:24:05,907 --> 01:24:07,542
WAS INSIDE YOU. THERE WERE NO DRUGS.

957
01:24:07,575 --> 01:24:11,379
- YOU'RE LYIN'. - IT WAS ALWAYS YOU, IAN.

958
01:24:16,384 --> 01:24:20,522
CALL THE POLICE. HE'S GONE OFF TO KILL HIS LAWYER.

959
01:24:29,864 --> 01:24:32,233
JOE, WHAT IS IT?

960
01:24:32,267 --> 01:24:35,270
WE HAVE TO TALK. IT'S ABOUT IAN.

961
01:24:42,944 --> 01:24:45,613
WHAT'S SO IMPORTANT, IT COULDN'T WAIT TILL MORNING?

962
01:24:45,647 --> 01:24:49,751
RELAX. WHY DON'T YOU GO FIX US A COUPLE OF DRINKS?

963
01:24:52,587 --> 01:24:56,591
JOE, I REALLY DON'T THINK THAT'S APPROPRIATE.

964
01:24:56,624 --> 01:25:00,628
YOU REALLY THINK I ENJOY DRIVIN' ACROSS TOWN THIS TIME OF NIGHT?

965
01:25:00,662 --> 01:25:03,798
I'M JUST TRYIN' TO HELP HERE.

966
01:25:03,832 --> 01:25:05,500
SORRY.

967
01:25:05,533 --> 01:25:08,603
ALL THIS STUFF WITH IAN IS MOVING SO FAST.

968
01:25:08,636 --> 01:25:11,639
WELL, ONCE THE PAPERS ARE SIGNED,

969
01:25:11,673 --> 01:25:13,608
IT'LL BE OVER.

970
01:25:13,641 --> 01:25:15,243
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

971
01:25:15,276 --> 01:25:16,911
I WAS THINKING.

972
01:25:16,945 --> 01:25:20,548
